headline: Robinhood pops on Morgan Stanley upgrade and target lift
summary: Morgan Stanley upgrades Robinhood (HOOD) to Overweight from Equal-weight and lifts its price to $55 from $24. The analysts indicate Robinhood is positioned to gain from the election-fueled rally. Market Domination Hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton take a look at the note and what analysts say about the stock. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here. This post was written by Naomi Buchanan.

headline: Robinhood Stock Has ‘More Room to Run’ After Doubling This Year
summary: Shares of  Robinhood Markets  rose after a  Morgan Stanley  analyst more than doubled his target for the stock’s price, citing a revival of “animal spirits” and favorable conditions for cryptocurrencies under the second Trump administration.  The stock was up 4% to $38 Monday, putting it on pace for its best month on record, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  Analyst Michael Cyprys upgraded the shares to Overweight from Equal Weight and raised his price target to $55 from $24.
